 "article": {
  "headline": "Morocco send Canada crashing out of World Cup",
  "description": "Azzedine Ounahi scored twice in the second half as Morocco beat co-hosts Canada 3-0 in Houston to book their place in the World Cup quarterfinals.",
  "story": "<p><photo caption=\"Morocco beat Canada 3-0 in the World Cup round of 16.\"></p>\n<p><a data-player-guid=\"6352a5df-7c1e-ec8d-bf58-f4dafa55e69b\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/player/_/id/291552/azzedine-ounahi\">Azzedine Ounahi</a> scored twice in the second half as <a data-clubhouse-guid=\"a6945df8-27b1-9615-af13-7379154954b9\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/team?id=2869\">Morocco</a> beat co-hosts <a data-clubhouse-guid=\"c09eeeeb-7c2d-23f9-1bbf-153ff7e59905\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/team?id=206\">Canada</a> 3-0 in Houston to book their place in the World Cup quarterfinals.</p>\n<p>Morocco, semifinalists in <a data-clubhouse-guid=\"9e775b11-9fbd-ae9c-d590-9d3e892188f7\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/team?id=4398\">Qatar</a> four years ago, had been second best during the first half as Canadian-born goalkeeper <a data-player-guid=\"ec62cfce-f0d0-3a90-7e94-7a2ba13a1336\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/player/_/id/175149/yassine-bounou\">Yassine Bounou</a> denied both <a data-player-guid=\"508c0892-be59-17f4-0c11-88b8fbf65646\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/player/_/id/273499/jonathan-david\">Jonathan David</a> and <a data-player-guid=\"1f76a642-c780-3483-b2ea-1e98c511ce70\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/player/_/id/294039/tani-oluwaseyi\">Tani Oluwaseyi</a> early on.</p>\n<p>Girona midfielder Ounahi eventually broke the deadlock five minutes after the restart when he swept in a low shot following a well-worked free-kick and then added a late second on the break before <a data-player-guid=\"23feefb5-c5d9-8276-4383-1e7337dcd980\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/player/_/id/276139/soufiane-rahimi\">Soufiane Rahimi</a> added a third in stoppage time to make sure of a place in the last eight against either <a data-clubhouse-guid=\"81be996c-0f98-eec4-6284-c6be0d186360\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/team?id=478\">France</a> or <a data-clubhouse-guid=\"67227b21-5b19-9dd2-b805-534045f412f9\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/team?id=210\">Paraguay</a>.</p>\n<p>Canada -- with star man <a data-player-guid=\"d41614d6-11bc-0e9b-d180-06dfff0d4ec6\" href=\"http://espn.com/soccer/player/_/id/236721/alphonso-davies\">Alphonso Davies</a> again on the bench -- had started brightly as Jonathan David's angled effort from an early corner was palmed away by Morocco keeper Bounou, who then produced a fine reaction save after Tani Oluwaseyi had burst into the penalty area.</p>\n<p>Morocco -- runners-up to <a data-clubhouse-guid=\"2a0"
 },
